**The bottom line:** Of the ~20 tools catalogued here, approximately **13 are buildable today with existing technology and no experimental validation required**. The remaining 7 require either significant compute resources (TDA on large landscapes) or open research problems (efficient Gröbner basis estimation, canonical statistical manifold embeddings). None require new scientific discoveries — only engineering.
